				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I read that, my sarcasm-o-meter went off.  It seemed that the Cylin was probably just kidding about restricting it to wolf warders only.  As far as the race/class combo restrictions I think the difference is that those are quested items that give them those powers, not inherent abilities as Eatbugs mentioned.  If a troll shaman want's the darkness snare, he's got to go through the 3step quest to get it.
<br />

<br />
I admit I would like track for the "rightness" of it from a logical perspective, who better to understand the signs of an animal's movements than one devoted to their understanding and mastery.  It rankles my pride to have to ask a softskin to track for me.  I do wish that there was at least one dark race or class that could track, even if it wasn't Iksar beastlords.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />   Unfortunately, I do see the potential to that being abused or unbalancing.
<br />

<br />
Maybe track could be considered as a class AA.  It's not obscene, and it wouldn't be common as dirt, and finally the "black hats" wouldn't have to eat crow and beg some druid, ranger, or bard to track for them.<br />_________________<br /><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411225">Draig</A>, Iksar Beastlord (52)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
